中華民國比較文學學會claroc100@gmail.comyundong2015taiwanrenwenxueshelilunying1https://sites.google.com/feeds/content/site/claroc100/55622648404788706042014-10-07T01:43:05.410Z2014-10-22T01:04:27.629Z2014-10-22T01:04:26.192Z兒童文學的典範轉移 研討會「兒童文學的典範轉移」研討會Shifting Paradigms in Children’s Literature 報名請洽會議網站： https://sites.google.com/site/tclra2014/ 會議日期：2014年11月8日會議地點已改於：東吳大學外雙溪校區（111臺北市士林區臨溪路70號）根據孔恩（Thomas Kuhn） 的說法，當異例（即不符合典範所預期的現象）的出現強迫某個學科社群必須重新思索該領域的基本假設，甚至進而調整基本的價值與方法論時，典範轉移的契機就 出現了。幾十年來，新興科技、「兒童」觀念的改變、「童年」定義的變動，以及人們對於全球與當地社群的新觀感，一再為兒童文學帶來新的局面：不僅童書有所 改變，人們（包括兒童與成人）與童書之間的互動關係也已經大不相同。這些情況為兒童文學專業人員帶來重新省思研究方法、研究範疇、與研究目的等等的挑戰。Conference Date: November 8, 2014Conference Venue has been changed to: Waishuangxi Campus, Soochow University A
 paradigm shift happens, according to Thomas Kuhn, when agents of change
 force those within an academic discipline to rethink their fundamental 
assumptions. In
 the field of children’s literature, developing technologies, new ways 
of understanding global and local communities, and changing notions of 
children and childhood have brought changes to texts for children as 
well as the ways children and other users interact with them. This, in 
turn, challenges professionals who work with children’s texts to 
reconsider their methods, scope, and purpose. The purpose of this 
conference is to interrogate ways in which the paradigms related to the 
study and development of children’s literature are shifting.中華民國比較文學學會claroc100@gmail.comertongwenxuededianfanzhuanyiyantaohui3



















